(text "NOTES:" (at 20.32 330.2 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid a92275b5-7517-5b08-9328-2029ad3ca555))
(text "Mu VIN and onboard eDP BL_PWR use regulated MU_12V; the exact B160QAN03.K harness/pinout remains a release gate." (at 20.32 337.82 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid fba3ba8e-ace0-5731-8a05-e898c3d17633))
(text "Default-BIOS HSIO0/1 are independent native USB 3.2 Gen2 ports; HSIO3 + USB2_P1 feed M.2 E-key." (at 20.32 345.44 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 74b57cc3-b76f-5a1f-8a40-5a3bcc39f014))
(text "The verified B160QAN03.K panel connects to the Mu onboard eDP connector; DDIB is unused." (at 20.32 354.33 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 09f6684b-d608-577c-b709-68b202b3cf6c))
(text "TCP0 HDMI 2.0 lane/HPD/DDC nets leave to sheet 6 for the external HDMI-A output." (at 20.32 361.95 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 18cfbbd0-6438-55c6-b56c-17be4ff624c2))
(text "USB2_P3 is EC; P4 pairs with USB-C 2; P5 is the system-audio hub; P7 is maker MCU; P8 is trackpad." (at 20.32 369.57 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid fd153979-cd6d-5619-b8fd-09de1570ef05))
(text "Native USB-C data/OC nets leave to sheet 4; VBUS switching, CC, muxing, and ESD live there." (at 20.32 378.46 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid a59220b9-65e5-5881-8c19-7d3b786e3453))
(text "SYS_5V and SYS_3V3 use TPS56637 6A-class bucks with XAL7070 inductors; endpoint load budgets remain a release check." (at 20.32 386.08 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 4bbb0795-a7ce-5046-a5b0-37e5a70a75e3))
(text "M.2 M-key uses default HSIO8-11 x4 and REFCLK2; no lane reversal and no TX/RX direction swap." (at 20.32 393.7 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 7285d77f-f0e9-5dbd-9f05-22a85ae63849))
(text "M.2 M-key: Mu TX->PET through 220n near J10; PET/PER naming is from the host perspective." (at 20.32 401.32 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid f4731773-ab46-520b-a0f0-9092455c6429))
(text "USB2_P6 is reserved for the Mu Type-C PD controller direction; trackpad consumes the former USB2_P8 spare." (at 20.32 408.94 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid e1674207-f4d0-5266-9f1d-63a5782c67c3))
(text "MU_12V is a TPS552892EVM-derived 12V stage: 400kHz forced PWM, 3.33A nominal limit, and about 8.65-9.40V worst-case rising UVLO. Firmware requires VSYS >=10.0V." (at 20.32 416.56 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid bb3caf01-5f7a-506a-868f-41ef810501d5))
(text "MU_12V_ENABLE is active high and defaults low. Q750/Q751 force EN/UVLO low until EC firmware explicitly releases the rail; MU_12V_PG is pulled up to MCU_3V3." (at 20.32 424.18 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid c8aaee34-7a48-5104-926f-0fcc137dc99d))
(text "POWER BUDGET HOLD: MU_12V is about 40W maximum for Mu plus eDP backlight. Lock BIOS PL1/PL2 only after measuring panel and whole-module draw; unrestricted 35W CPU mode is not released." (at 20.32 431.8 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 22e95a6c-3d67-5a19-81be-b8a4b15e387e))
(text "MU_S0_HIGH is Mu PSON with the required 10k pull-up to always-on MCU_3V3. It is a weak status signal for logic/NMOS gates only, never a load supply." (at 20.32 439.42 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 8120eb3f-12aa-5842-8b19-b1f96bb2b8b7))
(text "SLEEP POLICY: PSON is low in S3, so PCIe endpoint 3V3, user USB-C VBUS, trackpad, maker USB, and internal audio detach. Wake from those devices is intentionally unsupported." (at 20.32 447.04 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 577ed8b4-3ab4-5ff2-8d62-840b462da4fb))
(text "MECHANICAL: the 8.0mm standard-orientation TE 2309411-1 socket requires two grounded 5.5mm M2 standoffs at H1/H2; SO-DIMM clips alone are not structural retention." (at 20.32 454.66 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 43cbf13a-a92f-5725-a97e-d69793c79cb4))
(text "MECHANICAL: H3 is the grounded 2280 retainer for the 4.2mm M-key socket. H10-H17 are isolated M2.5 chassis holes; chassis bonding is a separate controlled point." (at 20.32 462.28 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid c1e4e25a-5c66-59c7-9c1b-efd14298bc59))
